# OpenSpec (Fission-AI/OpenSpec) — track project artifacts as source of truth
# Currently tracked: config.yaml (skeleton/seed; specs/ changes/ not yet used)
# Future: specs/ (source of truth), changes incl archive/ (proposals + audit),
#         schemas/, README.md — tracked when first created
# Tool configs (openspec writes to .claude/.cursor/) stay ignored by rules above.

# Spec-Kit (specify CLI + superspec bridge)
# Track: constitution, specs, templates, workflows
# Ignore: installed extension code, helper scripts, regenerable caches, and manifests
# Exception: project-owned extensions ship in-tree (spec 012 US3, FR-014) —
# external cloned extensions (superspec etc.) stay ignored.
.specify/extensions/*
!.specify/extensions/vibe-spec-bridge/
.specify/extensions/vibe-spec-bridge/.specify-dev/
.specify/scripts/
.specify/integrations/
.specify/init-options.json
# superpowers.yml: detection cache, regenerated by /speckit.superspec.status
.specify/superpowers.yml

